    <p>I am one half of indie-folk songwriting duo <a href="https://forestfloormusic.com/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener" aria-label="This is an external link (opens in a new tab)">forestfloor</a>. We make thoughtful and arresting unplugged music for fans of Bon Iver, Fairport Convention, Dirty Projectors, Adrianne Lenker, Radiohead.</p>

    <p>Prior to forestfloor my music projects date back to 2001:</p>

    <ul>
        <li>Solo performer - while at art school in Kingston I joined an experimental music collective combining classical, folk and post-rock styles. I wrote introspective songs around fingerstyle acoustic guitar in open tunings. This period culminated in playing at Glastonbury Festival in 2008.</li>
        <li>Music producer - after moving back to Folkestone I self-produced many EPs and albums of brooding, atmospheric folktronica. I translated my multi-instrumental compositions to the stage using live-looping techniques.</li>
        <li>Boo, Forever - a collaborative project with Si Norton, Ben Fletcher, Natalie Evans and Rebecca Aimi. We shared songwriting duties and I produced our eponymous album, released on vinyl in 2013 by Something Something Records.</li>
        <li>Minor Planet - my rap alter ego. I made a playful alternative hip-hop album and shot some videos with local filmmaker Joel Snowman, capturing a common experience of our home town from the fringes.</li>
    </ul>

    

